{
    "publish_date": "2012-08-13T15:14:31.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT5M", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "(Guitar music throughout)", 
            "dur": "1.701", 
            "start": "15.489"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Music is a language.", 
            "dur": "1.798", 
            "start": "19.906"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Both music and verbal languages\nserve the same purpose.", 
            "dur": "3.684", 
            "start": "22.893"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They are both forms of expression.", 
            "dur": "2.065", 
            "start": "26.601"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They can be used as a way\nto communicate with others.", 
            "dur": "2.904", 
            "start": "29.857"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They can be read and written.", 
            "dur": "1.867", 
            "start": "33.615"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They can make you laugh or cry,", 
            "dur": "1.824", 
            "start": "36.819"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "think or question,", 
            "dur": "1.232", 
            "start": "38.667"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and can speak to one or many.", 
            "dur": "2.107", 
            "start": "39.923"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And both can definitely make you move.", 
            "dur": "2.718", 
            "start": "43.586"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In some instances, music works\nbetter than the spoken word,", 
            "dur": "3.307", 
            "start": "50.241"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because it doesn&#39;t have\nto be understood to be effective.", 
            "dur": "3.315", 
            "start": "53.572"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Although many musicians agree\nthat music is a language,", 
            "dur": "3.039", 
            "start": "59.386"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it is rarely treated as such.", 
            "dur": "2.085", 
            "start": "62.449"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Many of us treat it as something", 
            "dur": "1.601", 
            "start": "65.524"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that can only be learned\nby following a strict regimen,", 
            "dur": "2.976", 
            "start": "67.149"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "under the tutelage of a skilled teacher.", 
            "dur": "2.106", 
            "start": "70.149"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This approach has been followed\nfor hundreds of years", 
            "dur": "2.623", 
            "start": "73.455"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with proven success,\nbut it takes a long time.", 
            "dur": "4.092", 
            "start": "76.102"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Too long.", 
            "dur": "1.179", 
            "start": "81.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Think about the first language\nyou learn as a child.", 
            "dur": "3.575", 
            "start": "90.657"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "More importantly,\nthink about how you learned it.", 
            "dur": "2.755", 
            "start": "94.256"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You were a baby\nwhen you first started speaking,", 
            "dur": "2.239", 
            "start": "99.038"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and even though you spoke\nthe language incorrectly", 
            "dur": "2.393", 
            "start": "101.301"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you were allowed to make mistakes.", 
            "dur": "1.682", 
            "start": "103.718"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the more mistakes you made,", 
            "dur": "2.23", 
            "start": "105.424"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the more your parents smiled.", 
            "dur": "2.162", 
            "start": "107.678"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Learning to speak was not something\nyou were sent somewhere to do", 
            "dur": "3.096", 
            "start": "114.676"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "only a few times a week.", 
            "dur": "1.83", 
            "start": "117.796"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the majority\nof the people you spoke to", 
            "dur": "2.048", 
            "start": "119.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "were not beginners.", 
            "dur": "1.328", 
            "start": "121.722"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They were already proficient speakers.", 
            "dur": "2.439", 
            "start": "123.074"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Imagine your parents forcing you\nto only speak to other babies", 
            "dur": "3.125", 
            "start": "127.473"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "until you were good enough\nto speak to them.", 
            "dur": "2.243", 
            "start": "130.622"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You would probably be an adult before\nyou could carry on a proper conversation.", 
            "dur": "4.484", 
            "start": "134.966"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To use a musical term,", 
            "dur": "1.422", 
            "start": "141.955"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as a baby, you were allowed\nto jam with professionals.", 
            "dur": "4.507", 
            "start": "143.401"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If we approach music\nin the same natural way", 
            "dur": "2.83", 
            "start": "156.366"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we approached our first language,", 
            "dur": "1.877", 
            "start": "159.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we will learn to speak it\nin the same short time", 
            "dur": "2.286", 
            "start": "161.121"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it took to speak our first language.", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "163.431"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Proof of this could be\nseen in almost any family", 
            "dur": "2.512", 
            "start": "165.575"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where a child grows up\nwith other musicians in the family.", 
            "dur": "3.413", 
            "start": "168.111"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here are a few keys to follow\nin learning or teaching music.", 
            "dur": "3.239", 
            "start": "206.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the beginning, embrace mistakes,\ninstead of correcting them.", 
            "dur": "3.519", 
            "start": "211.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Like a child playing air guitar,\nthere are no wrong notes.", 
            "dur": "4.069", 
            "start": "216.245"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Allow young musicians to play", 
            "dur": "1.849", 
            "start": "222.172"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and perform with accomplished musicians", 
            "dur": "2.027", 
            "start": "224.045"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on a daily basis.", 
            "dur": "1.086", 
            "start": "226.096"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Encourage young musicians to play\nmore than they practice.", 
            "dur": "4.091", 
            "start": "228.533"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The more they play the more\nthey will practice on their own.", 
            "dur": "3.643", 
            "start": "232.648"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Music comes from the musician,\nnot the instrument.", 
            "dur": "2.914", 
            "start": "236.315"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And most importantly,", 
            "dur": "1.665", 
            "start": "241.752"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "remember that a language works best", 
            "dur": "2.969", 
            "start": "243.441"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when we have something interesting to say.", 
            "dur": "2.327", 
            "start": "246.434"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Many music teachers never find out\nwhat their students have to say.", 
            "dur": "3.226", 
            "start": "249.759"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We only tell them\nwhat they are supposed to say.", 
            "dur": "3.231", 
            "start": "253.009"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A child speaks a language for years\nbefore they even learn the alphabet.", 
            "dur": "4.219", 
            "start": "261.088"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Too many rules at the onset,\nwill actually slow them down.", 
            "dur": "3.318", 
            "start": "266.229"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In my eyes, the approach to music\nshould be the same.", 
            "dur": "3.88", 
            "start": "271.158"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "After all, music is a language too.", 
            "dur": "2.924", 
            "start": "276.194"
        }
    ], 
